20@2@All this was new and interesting; that is, for the first time, but afterwards, as the weather-cock found out, they repeated themselves and always told the same stories, and that's very tedious, and there was no one with whom one could associate, for one and all were stale and small-minded.
21@2@"The world is no good!" he said.
22@2@"Everything in it is so stupid."
39@2@"Everything is very stupid," the weather-cock said to himself.
42@2@Everything is so stupid!
43@2@I don't want to sit here any longer."
